

What I actually did:
Today was all execution. Theory was done yesterday so the focus shifted to
getting the three classifiers running properly end to end. Ran Decision Tree,
kNN, and Naive Bayes on Titanic, Wine, and Breast Cancer datasets. Titanic was
already preprocessed from yesterday so Wine and Breast Cancer were quicker —
both load directly from sklearn so no manual cleaning needed.

Built a pipeline for each classifier wrapping StandardScaler with the model.
Kept the structure consistent across all three so comparison was clean.
Plotted confusion matrices for each model across each dataset. Decision Tree
needed max_depth tuning — without it confusion matrix showed clear overfitting.
kNN settled on k=7 after testing a range. Naive Bayes needed the least tuning,
ran well out of the box on all three datasets.

Wrote the performance comparison summary covering accuracy, F1 score, and
confusion matrix observations for each model. Noted where class imbalance
affected results and flagged Titanic specifically for the capstone.

